      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Patios Built for This Climate</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A patio in the desert needs to handle extremes: 100-degree surface temperatures in summer, freezing nights in winter, and monsoon downpours that dump an inch of rain in twenty minutes. Materials that work in other climates crack, shift, or pool water here if the base isn't right.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">We start every patio with proper excavation, compacted base material, and drainage grading. Then we build with materials suited to the UV exposure and temperature range — flagstone, concrete pavers, stamped concrete, or natural stone, depending on your space and your taste.</p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
